# Security Rules

## Authentication

- bcrypt cost factor 12 for passwords.
- JWT access short-lived (15m); refresh tokens hashed (SHA-256) in DB.
- Revoke refresh tokens on logout.

## Authorization

- RBAC via `UserRole` + `Permission` — check with `PermissionsGuard`.
- Resource access must scope to `operatorId` from JWT.

## API

- Helmet enabled. CORS allowlist from env.
- Rate limit auth endpoints (add middleware in hardening phase).
- Validate all inputs with Zod.

## Secrets

- Never commit `.env`. Use Railway/Vercel secret managers in production.
- Rotate JWT secrets on compromise.

## Files

- Allowlist MIME: jpeg, png, pdf. Max 10MB.
- S3 SSE-KMS in production (AWS phase).

## Socket.io

- JWT auth on connection before room join (production requirement).

## Dependencies

- Run `pnpm audit` in CI. Patch critical within 48h.
